[NARRATOR A] Neo Tokyo.
Year Twenty Double X.

00:00:19.686 --> 00:00:21.229 position:50% align:center
Rebelling against a social order

00:00:21.312 --> 00:00:23.523 position:50% align:center
they felt had bankrupted
their future,

00:00:23.606 --> 00:00:26.985 position:50% align:center
young people everywhere cast
off the yoke of civilization

00:00:27.068 --> 00:00:30.447 position:50% align:center
and formed restless,
exclusionary tribes.

00:00:30.530 --> 00:00:33.908 position:50% align:center
Fierce. Proud. Warlike.

00:00:33.992 --> 00:00:35.994 position:50% align:center
Inevitably, this
partisan zeal gave way

00:00:36.077 --> 00:00:38.288 position:50% align:center
to blistering
sectarian violence,

00:00:38.371 --> 00:00:41.124 position:50% align:center
transforming the country
into an abattoir.

00:00:41.207 --> 00:00:45.295 position:50% align:center
No one was safe. The world
was steeped in blood.

00:00:45.378 --> 00:00:47.756 position:50% align:center
Desperate to contain the
mounting pandemonium,

00:00:47.839 --> 00:00:49.674 position:50% align:center
Neo Tokyo's government mandated

00:00:49.758 --> 00:00:52.135 position:50% align:center
that all inter-tribal
disputes be resolved

00:00:52.218 --> 00:00:54.637 position:50% align:center
through specially
curated conflicts.

00:00:54.721 --> 00:00:59.768 position:50% align:center
Dubbed: Extreme Baseball.

00:00:59.851 --> 00:01:03.396 position:50% align:center
This was known
colloquially as "XB Law."

00:01:03.480 --> 00:01:06.566 position:50% align:center
As one might expect,
with their pride on the line,

00:01:06.649 --> 00:01:09.361 position:50% align:center
the nation's youth poured its
collective heart and soul

00:01:09.444 --> 00:01:13.573 position:50% align:center
into this minacious,
high-tech sport.

00:01:25.418 --> 00:01:27.003 position:50% align:center
