[HARU, TAIGA yelp]

00:11:29.064 --> 00:11:30.899 position:50% align:center
All aboard!

00:11:38.782 --> 00:11:40.825 position:50% align:center
[HARU]
Wait! What're you doing?

00:11:40.909 --> 00:11:43.620 position:50% align:center
[TAIGA]
Yeah! Livin' the dream!

00:11:43.703 --> 00:11:45.747 position:50% align:center
Huh? What is that?

00:11:45.830 --> 00:11:50.085 position:50% align:center
An XB umpire. Think of
it like a judge-y robot.

00:11:50.168 --> 00:11:51.211 position:50% align:center
Power's good!

00:11:51.294 --> 00:11:52.629 position:50% align:center
Hydraulics're good!

00:11:52.712 --> 00:11:54.005 position:50% align:center
Safety's good!

00:11:54.089 --> 00:11:55.340 position:50% align:center
Everything's good!

00:11:55.423 --> 00:11:56.883 position:50% align:center
Am I seeing things?

00:11:56.966 --> 00:12:00.929 position:50% align:center
No worries. Just a part of our
lineup. They're quadruplets!

00:12:01.012 --> 00:12:03.682 position:50% align:center
Right. Bench open, now!

00:12:12.816 --> 00:12:14.275 position:50% align:center
[HARU]
Wow.

00:12:14.359 --> 00:12:17.320 position:50% align:center
[SANTAROU] I present to you
the Minato Tribe's mobile bench.

00:12:17.404 --> 00:12:20.657 position:50% align:center
Awesome!

00:12:20.740 --> 00:12:25.245 position:50% align:center
[SHUN]
Alrighty then, let's play ball.

00:12:26.955 --> 00:12:30.000 position:50% align:center
[SAORI] Here ya go.
Can't play in street clothes.

00:12:30.083 --> 00:12:32.002 position:50% align:center
I... can't play at all.

00:12:32.085 --> 00:12:34.504 position:50% align:center
[SAORI]
Uh-huh. Whatever you say.

00:12:34.587 --> 00:12:35.797 position:50% align:center
You'll want these.

00:12:35.880 --> 00:12:38.967 position:50% align:center
One transmit badge and
one bracelet glove. Cool?

00:12:39.050 --> 00:12:41.594 position:50% align:center
It's only your basic
Extreme Baseball gear.

00:12:41.678 --> 00:12:44.222 position:50% align:center
I'm telling you,
I can't do this!

00:12:44.305 --> 00:12:44.931 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:12:45.015 --> 00:12:46.683 position:50% align:center
Quit bein' such a wimp.

00:12:46.766 --> 00:12:48.018 position:50% align:center
How do you know you can't play

00:12:48.101 --> 00:12:50.228 position:50% align:center
if you've never even
bothered to try?

00:12:50.311 --> 00:12:52.897 position:50% align:center
[HARU] But what if I'm
the reason we lose?

00:12:52.981 --> 00:12:53.982 position:50% align:center
Just try your best!

00:12:54.065 --> 00:12:55.859 position:50% align:center
[HARU groans]

00:12:55.942 --> 00:12:59.529 position:50% align:center
What about trying is such
a difficult concept?

00:12:59.612 --> 00:13:03.116 position:50% align:center
It's just an opportunity
for self-discovery, right?

00:13:04.743 --> 00:13:05.994 position:50% align:center
Quit it!

00:13:06.077 --> 00:13:08.747 position:50% align:center
It's all good. Leave this
to Joltin' Joe-Taiga!

00:13:08.830 --> 00:13:12.167 position:50% align:center
[SAORI] For now, you guys just
remember one simple thing.

00:13:12.250 --> 00:13:15.420 position:50% align:center
Once you've got the
ball, crush them!

00:13:15.503 --> 00:13:17.964 position:50% align:center
Like, beat 'em up?
Oh-ho-ho, yes!

00:13:18.048 --> 00:13:19.174 position:50% align:center
Watch your backs.

00:13:19.257 --> 00:13:22.135 position:50% align:center
The opposing team will
get just as violent.

00:13:22.218 --> 00:13:24.721 position:50% align:center
Okay! Let's get up and running!

00:13:24.804 --> 00:13:26.014 position:50% align:center
[SANTAROU]
You got it!

00:13:26.097 --> 00:13:28.725 position:50% align:center
Um, so, like, what
position do you play?

00:13:28.808 --> 00:13:31.227 position:50% align:center
Oh. Have a look.

00:13:35.357 --> 00:13:36.024 position:50% align:center
Catcher.

00:13:36.107 --> 00:13:37.359 position:50% align:center
Ahh.

00:13:37.442 --> 00:13:40.528 position:50% align:center
Yup. Saori's also the best
playmaker in the game.

00:13:40.612 --> 00:13:41.863 position:50% align:center
[HARU]
Playmaker?

00:13:41.946 --> 00:13:43.782 position:50% align:center
[MANAMI] Physically,
she's an absolute beast.

00:13:43.865 --> 00:13:45.617 position:50% align:center
Mentally, she's a supercomputer.

00:13:45.700 --> 00:13:47.786 position:50% align:center
It takes a certain kind of
person to catch Shun's pitches

00:13:47.869 --> 00:13:50.413 position:50% align:center
when he's serious, and she's it.

00:13:51.414 --> 00:13:53.333 position:50% align:center
[JUDGE ROBOT]
Play ball!

00:14:01.758 --> 00:14:03.218 position:50% align:center
[SAORI]
Perfect.

00:14:05.178 --> 00:14:07.097 position:50% align:center
[SAORI gasps]

00:14:07.180 --> 00:14:08.348 position:50% align:center
There it goes!

00:14:08.431 --> 00:14:10.684 position:50% align:center
Fifty meters north of
Block 3! Track it down!

00:14:10.767 --> 00:14:13.353 position:50% align:center
[JIRO]
I got it! Going to cut it off!

00:14:28.326 --> 00:14:30.954 position:50% align:center
Uh! Incoming!

00:14:31.037 --> 00:14:32.580 position:50% align:center
[yelling]

00:14:32.664 --> 00:14:33.915 position:50% align:center
The hell d'ya think
you're doing?!

00:14:33.998 --> 00:14:36.459 position:50% align:center
[TAIGA] You're not
goin' anywhere, lass!

00:14:38.712 --> 00:14:39.879 position:50% align:center
Idiot!

00:14:39.963 --> 00:14:41.589 position:50% align:center
What? How's this legal?

00:14:41.673 --> 00:14:44.134 position:50% align:center
[screams]

00:14:44.217 --> 00:14:45.468 position:50% align:center
Interference!

00:14:45.552 --> 00:14:47.679 position:50% align:center
Physical contact
without possession!

00:14:47.762 --> 00:14:49.222 position:50% align:center
[SAORI] Did you or
did you not hear me say

00:14:49.305 --> 00:14:51.182 position:50% align:center
crush them after
you've got the ball?

00:14:51.266 --> 00:14:53.435 position:50% align:center
You're just handing
'em unearned runs!

00:14:53.518 --> 00:14:56.521 position:50% align:center
Got it! That one's
one me! Sorry!

00:14:58.732 --> 00:15:00.025 position:50% align:center
Totally the noob's fault.

00:15:00.108 --> 00:15:01.443 position:50% align:center
Definitely the noob's fault.

00:15:01.526 --> 00:15:03.069 position:50% align:center
Absolutely the noob's fault.

00:15:03.153 --> 00:15:04.904 position:50% align:center
No question the noob's fault.

00:15:04.988 --> 00:15:06.781 position:50% align:center
All right! We get it!

00:15:06.865 --> 00:15:09.743 position:50% align:center
[MANAMI]
Okay, Haru. You're up.

00:15:09.826 --> 00:15:11.786 position:50% align:center
No. Please. I can't.

00:15:11.870 --> 00:15:13.538 position:50% align:center
If all you're gonna
do is sit on your ass,

00:15:13.621 --> 00:15:15.165 position:50% align:center
let me go out there for you.

00:15:15.248 --> 00:15:16.541 position:50% align:center
Um, sure.

00:15:16.624 --> 00:15:18.335 position:50% align:center
Way to be worthy
of your nickname.

00:15:18.418 --> 00:15:19.627 position:50% align:center
[HARU]
Hm?

00:15:20.712 --> 00:15:21.963 position:50% align:center
[TAIGA]
You're never gonna win

00:15:22.047 --> 00:15:25.216 position:50% align:center
if you won't even
step up to the plate.

00:15:25.300 --> 00:15:26.801 position:50% align:center
I appreciate the advice,

00:15:26.885 --> 00:15:28.970 position:50% align:center
but not everyone's as keen
on picking random fights

00:15:29.054 --> 00:15:30.263 position:50% align:center
like you are.

00:15:30.347 --> 00:15:31.473 position:50% align:center
Well then, by all means,

00:15:31.556 --> 00:15:33.892 position:50% align:center
keep sucking your thumb
from the sidelines,

00:15:33.975 --> 00:15:35.769 position:50% align:center
"Mega Boring."

00:15:35.852 --> 00:15:38.855 position:50% align:center
Oooh, someone's nickname
just leveled up.

00:15:41.649 --> 00:15:44.194 position:50% align:center
C'mon! Let's do it!

00:15:44.277 --> 00:15:46.404 position:50% align:center
[YUTAKA]
Ah, blunt and stupid.

00:15:46.488 --> 00:15:47.906 position:50% align:center
I adore the simple types.

00:15:47.989 --> 00:15:50.784 position:50% align:center
Predicting their
moves is so easy!

00:15:50.867 --> 00:15:51.659 position:50% align:center
[TAIGA yells]

00:15:51.743 --> 00:15:52.744 position:50% align:center
[JUDGE ROBOT]
Strike!

00:15:52.827 --> 00:15:55.246 position:50% align:center
Oh. Yikes!

00:15:55.330 --> 00:15:57.957 position:50% align:center
It ain't over yet!

00:15:58.041 --> 00:15:58.833 position:50% align:center
[JUDGE ROBOT]
Strike!

00:15:58.917 --> 00:16:00.085 position:50% align:center
[MANAMI]
Dial it back, Taiga!

00:16:00.168 --> 00:16:02.003 position:50% align:center
You're gonna swing
right out of your cleats!

00:16:02.087 --> 00:16:04.923 position:50% align:center
[TAIGA]
No way. Trust me on this.

00:16:05.006 --> 00:16:07.717 position:50% align:center
You wanna catch a fish,
you gotta set your hooks right.

00:16:07.801 --> 00:16:10.679 position:50% align:center
Tuna don't mess with
bait thrown by a wuss.

00:16:10.762 --> 00:16:12.305 position:50% align:center
Same deal here.

00:16:12.389 --> 00:16:14.974 position:50% align:center
Why even bother to play if
you're not gonna go all out?

00:16:15.058 --> 00:16:17.852 position:50% align:center
Playing not to lose
is a loser's game!

00:16:17.936 --> 00:16:19.979 position:50% align:center
Beautifully said.

00:16:20.063 --> 00:16:22.941 position:50% align:center
I believe we're
about to see a hit.

00:16:23.024 --> 00:16:24.526 position:50% align:center
[yells]

00:16:28.154 --> 00:16:30.281 position:50% align:center
[HARU gasps]

00:16:39.040 --> 00:16:40.500 position:50% align:center
[HARU gasps]

00:16:40.583 --> 00:16:43.294 position:50% align:center
Heave-ho!

00:16:43.378 --> 00:16:46.131 position:50% align:center
[yells]

00:16:47.340 --> 00:16:48.508 position:50% align:center
Blast.

00:16:48.591 --> 00:16:51.678 position:50% align:center
Nothing to worry about.
Just stop him at first.

00:16:53.221 --> 00:16:56.516 position:50% align:center
[yelling]

00:17:01.021 --> 00:17:05.734 position:50% align:center
Home run!

00:17:08.403 --> 00:17:10.280 position:50% align:center
[TAIGA]
Ha! Hell yeah!

00:17:10.363 --> 00:17:12.115 position:50% align:center
Tuna fisherman, baby!

00:17:12.198 --> 00:17:15.869 position:50% align:center
[laughing]

00:17:15.952 --> 00:17:19.414 position:50% align:center
So, you saw the ocean, too?

00:17:19.497 --> 00:17:21.833 position:50% align:center
Good. 'Cause it's your turn.

00:17:21.916 --> 00:17:23.460 position:50% align:center
What? But I told you I--!

00:17:23.543 --> 00:17:26.963 position:50% align:center
You really need to get over
this reluctance to try.

00:17:27.047 --> 00:17:30.717 position:50% align:center
You're allowed to find your
own way of being great.

00:17:35.013 --> 00:17:37.807 position:50% align:center
Just gotta keep
my eyes on the ball.

00:17:37.891 --> 00:17:40.185 position:50% align:center
Focus on that for now.

00:17:40.268 --> 00:17:43.355 position:50% align:center
[HARU]
Huh? My strong point? I don't...

00:17:43.438 --> 00:17:46.608 position:50% align:center
Yup. You've got way better
eyes than you think.

00:17:46.691 --> 00:17:48.693 position:50% align:center
The trick is
learning how to see.

00:17:48.777 --> 00:17:51.654 position:50% align:center
Just keep them open
and use them both.

00:17:51.738 --> 00:17:53.156 position:50% align:center
You got this.

00:17:53.239 --> 00:17:56.993 position:50% align:center
It'll be like experiencing
the world for the first time.

00:17:57.077 --> 00:17:59.079 position:50% align:center
[YUTAKA]
Quite a stance you've got.

00:17:59.162 --> 00:18:02.165 position:50% align:center
Should be easy enough
to work around.

00:18:03.166 --> 00:18:06.044 position:50% align:center
[HARU]
Use both eyes! Use both eyes!

00:18:08.088 --> 00:18:08.797 position:50% align:center
Look out!

00:18:08.880 --> 00:18:11.508 position:50% align:center
C'mon! Dodge it!

00:18:11.591 --> 00:18:12.967 position:50% align:center
[MANAMI, TAIGA gasp]

00:18:18.056 --> 00:18:19.099 position:50% align:center
Haru!

00:18:19.182 --> 00:18:20.767 position:50% align:center
Um, now what?

00:18:20.850 --> 00:18:22.227 position:50% align:center
[JUDGE ROBOT]
Run!

00:18:24.521 --> 00:18:27.232 position:50% align:center
[HARU]
Unbelievable! I hit it!

00:18:29.484 --> 00:18:32.237 position:50% align:center
[MINAMI] Sorry, sir. A program
error caused it to freeze.

00:18:32.320 --> 00:18:35.740 position:50% align:center
Shocking! This is what
happens when you outsource!

00:18:35.824 --> 00:18:37.409 position:50% align:center
Ugh. New plan.

00:18:37.492 --> 00:18:40.912 position:50% align:center
The ball's coming your way.
Stop him at first!

00:18:43.665 --> 00:18:45.709 position:50% align:center
[HARU yelps]

00:18:45.792 --> 00:18:48.378 position:50% align:center
[HARU] Oh, no.
This guy's gonna kill me!

00:18:48.461 --> 00:18:52.048 position:50% align:center
Seriously, I'm dead.
What do I do?

00:18:52.132 --> 00:18:54.384 position:50% align:center
[SHUN]
Just keep them open.

00:19:01.641 --> 00:19:03.435 position:50% align:center
[yells]

00:19:10.108 --> 00:19:12.861 position:50% align:center
[ALL cheer]

00:19:12.944 --> 00:19:16.823 position:50% align:center
[HARU]
I'm safe at first? For real?

00:19:16.906 --> 00:19:19.159 position:50% align:center
Hey, Boring. Nice one!

00:19:19.242 --> 00:19:21.411 position:50% align:center
They're a lot better than
I gave them credit for.

00:19:21.494 --> 00:19:22.829 position:50% align:center
[SHUN]
Mh-hm.

00:19:22.912 --> 00:19:24.539 position:50% align:center
How are your
instincts so on-point?

00:19:24.622 --> 00:19:27.083 position:50% align:center
[SHUN]
I dunno. Prob'ly luck.

00:19:27.167 --> 00:19:29.169 position:50% align:center
That said, I think it's
time I get out there

00:19:29.252 --> 00:19:31.004 position:50% align:center
and show 'em how
it's really done.

00:19:31.087 --> 00:19:34.549 position:50% align:center
Just let me worry about the
grounders. It's under control.

00:19:34.632 --> 00:19:37.469 position:50% align:center
If they think anyone else
is getting through-- Uh.

00:19:37.552 --> 00:19:41.848 position:50% align:center
Oh? Minato's big slugger.

00:19:41.931 --> 00:19:44.309 position:50% align:center
Do I remember
correctly, or like,

00:19:44.392 --> 00:19:47.687 position:50% align:center
can we win this by knocking
out your one and only pitcher?

00:19:47.771 --> 00:19:50.940 position:50% align:center
Oh, and is that such a
trivial matter to you?

00:19:51.983 --> 00:19:53.526 position:50% align:center
[SHUN]
Absolutely.

00:19:53.610 --> 00:19:55.528 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:19:55.612 --> 00:19:58.239 position:50% align:center
In that case, permit me
to set my pitching strength

00:19:58.323 --> 00:20:00.492 position:50% align:center
to maximum output.

00:20:06.498 --> 00:20:07.749 position:50% align:center
The hell's that?!

00:20:07.832 --> 00:20:11.670 position:50% align:center
Locked in.
Activating Mighty Mode.

00:20:11.753 --> 00:20:13.213 position:50% align:center
And behold!

00:20:13.296 --> 00:20:18.468 position:50% align:center
Our Tribe's latest technical
innovation: Gungnir Alpha!

00:20:18.551 --> 00:20:22.389 position:50% align:center
Reinforced artificial muscle
clocking in at 50 horsepower!

00:20:22.472 --> 00:20:24.057 position:50% align:center
And a high-powered plasma drum

00:20:24.140 --> 00:20:28.061 position:50% align:center
capable of launching
projectiles at railgun speed!

00:20:28.144 --> 00:20:30.313 position:50% align:center
Oh, man! That's tight!

00:20:30.397 --> 00:20:32.941 position:50% align:center
Seems a little bit unfair.

00:20:36.444 --> 00:20:38.655 position:50% align:center
But apparently legal.

00:20:45.787 --> 00:20:47.163 position:50% align:center
[SHUN]
Hmm.

00:20:53.420 --> 00:20:56.840 position:50% align:center
Goodness me. Too swift
for even your eagle eye?

00:20:56.923 --> 00:20:59.009 position:50% align:center
Ha! Dare to make contact
with this next one

00:20:59.092 --> 00:21:01.594 position:50% align:center
and the force will pummel
you into next week!

00:21:01.678 --> 00:21:02.679 position:50% align:center
Yeah?

00:21:02.762 --> 00:21:04.305 position:50% align:center
Or maybe I just
counter it hard enough

00:21:04.389 --> 00:21:06.599 position:50% align:center
to break the tip
off Minato Tower.

00:21:06.683 --> 00:21:08.268 position:50% align:center
That'd be impressive, too.

00:21:08.351 --> 00:21:10.395 position:50% align:center
Best of luck!

00:21:23.950 --> 00:21:25.285 position:50% align:center
[YUTAKA gasps]

00:21:25.368 --> 00:21:29.330 position:50% align:center
[screams]

00:21:35.295 --> 00:21:36.379 position:50% align:center
[HARU]
That's the moment I learned

00:21:36.463 --> 00:21:38.506 position:50% align:center
it wasn't just trash talk.

00:21:38.590 --> 00:21:40.633 position:50% align:center
These guys were serious.

00:21:40.717 --> 00:21:43.136 position:50% align:center
That day, I learned...

00:21:43.219 --> 00:21:47.515 position:50% align:center
...Extreme Baseball is
something to behold.

00:21:47.599 --> 00:21:49.059 position:50% align:center
I didn't know XB.

00:21:49.142 --> 00:21:51.895 position:50% align:center
I didn't wanna be the best.
I didn't wanna win.

00:21:51.978 --> 00:21:56.608 position:50% align:center
And if I'm being honest, I'm
still not even sure how you win.

00:21:56.691 --> 00:22:02.238 position:50% align:center
But standing there at first
base, watching that ball fly...

00:22:02.322 --> 00:22:05.241 position:50% align:center
...I knew I'd be playing
for the love of the game.

00:22:08.703 --> 00:22:09.662 position:50% align:center
[DELINQUENT A]
Dammit!

00:22:09.746 --> 00:22:12.290 position:50% align:center
Who's this Shun
Kamiya think he is?

00:22:12.374 --> 00:22:13.583 position:50% align:center
Take it easy.

00:22:13.667 --> 00:22:15.460 position:50% align:center
What? 'Scuse me?

00:22:15.543 --> 00:22:16.211 position:50% align:center
[DELINQUENT D]
Huh?

00:22:16.294 --> 00:22:18.088 position:50% align:center
[OTHERS]
Huh?

00:22:19.839 --> 00:22:21.091 position:50% align:center
[DELINQUENT A]
Well, lookie here!

00:22:21.174 --> 00:22:23.593 position:50% align:center
If it isn't widdle man himself.

00:22:23.677 --> 00:22:26.888 position:50% align:center
What's the matter?
No friends today?

00:22:26.971 --> 00:22:29.891 position:50% align:center
Ooh. Look at that.

00:22:30.850 --> 00:22:34.354 position:50% align:center
What? Ya got some
balls now kid?

00:22:34.437 --> 00:22:38.274 position:50% align:center
Heads up. I'm not
backing down anymore.

00:22:40.694 --> 00:22:47.117 position:50% align:center
[TAIGA grunting]

00:22:47.200 --> 00:22:48.910 position:50% align:center
[TAIGA]
Damn it! What am I doing here?

00:22:48.993 --> 00:22:50.120 position:50% align:center
I should've gone with him!

00:22:50.203 --> 00:22:52.747 position:50% align:center
He specifically said
to let him go alone.

00:22:52.831 --> 00:22:54.332 position:50% align:center
We have to respect that.

00:22:54.416 --> 00:22:56.292 position:50% align:center
But it's Haru.

00:22:58.545 --> 00:23:00.672 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Whoa! You're back!

00:23:00.755 --> 00:23:02.882 position:50% align:center
